 contemplating terminating such registration or listing.=E2=80=9D Foxconn t=
erminated the agreement on the grounds that the Nasdaq notice breached that=
 rep; Lordstown argues that it didn=E2=80=99t, and that anyway if it did it=
 was Foxconn=E2=80=99s fault.


  [3] "The Company timely tendered claims with respect to the SEC Investiga=
tion and Securities Actions to insurers under the applicable directors and =
officers (=E2=80=98D&O=E2=80=99) policies,=E2=80=9D says the bankruptcy dec=
laration. =E2=80=9CHowever, the Debtors=E2=80=99 primary and excess insurer=
s under the post-SPAC Merger D&O policy have taken the position that no cov=
erage is available for the vast majority of the Securities Actions and the =
SEC Investigation. The Company and its legal advisors have been and continu=
e to contest the insurers=E2=80=99 denial.=E2=80=9D


  [4] If you have not read Guy Lawson=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9COctopus,=E2=80=9D =
