ng those claimants. Here the claims are fairly simple, with no debt and lim=
ited operations. The question is how much of the money Lordstown has to pay=
 to its former shareholders (or the SEC) for getting their hopes up, and ho=
w much money it will have left to pay its current shareholders.</p>
